# NestJS Module Requirements

Every backend module under `apps/api/` must include:

| Layer | File pattern | Responsibility |
|-------|-------------|----------------|
| **Repository** | `*.repository.ts` | Prisma data access |
| **Service** | `*.service.ts` | Business logic, audit_log |
| **Controller** | `*.controller.ts` | HTTP routes, guards |
| **DTO** | `dto/*.dto.ts` | Request/response shapes |
| **Validation** | `class-validator` on DTOs | Input validation → 422 |
| **Swagger** | `@ApiTags` `@ApiOperation` | Document every endpoint |
| **Unit Test** | `*.service.spec.ts` | Service + repository logic |
| **E2E Test** | `test/*.e2e-spec.ts` | API integration via Playwright/Vitest |

## Module Checklist

```
modules/{name}/
  {name}.module.ts
  {name}.controller.ts
  {name}.service.ts
  {name}.repository.ts
  {name}.service.spec.ts
  dto/
    create-{name}.dto.ts
    update-{name}.dto.ts
```

## Patterns

- Controller → Service → Repository (never Prisma in controller)
- `@Permissions('module.resource.action')` on every route
- Response via global interceptor: `{ success, data, message }`
- Write operations call `AuditLogService.create()`
- Register module in `app.module.ts` and Swagger
